"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-sport-sport-olympics-olympics-2024-andrea-spendolini-sirieix-b1175057.html\", \"text\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies. Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search. See our privacy policy for more information.  Sport|Olympics  Andrea Spendolini-Sirieix has said she did not even want to alive in the wake of the Tokyo Olympics after finishing outside the medals in the 10metre platform diving competition.  Spendolini-Sirieix had a poor second dive in Tuesday's final and then was never really in contention in her quest for asecond medal after bronze in the synchro competitioneventually finishing in sixth place.  But the 19-year-old was tearful in the aftermath saying she felt lucky to be alive and competing in Paris.  She told the BBC: \\\"Obviously it wasn't the result that I wanted. I am not even upset with the competition. The girls dove amazing. They dove better than me today and it's because they work really hard.  \\\"I am not even upset with my performance. Three years ago, I did not even want to be alive, so today I am just happy that I am alive, I am breathing and I have got my family to support me.  \\\"My mum told me to just keep smiling and she said she was proud of me and they were here to see me. At the end of the day, that's all I can ask for,\\\" she added.  \\\"I am so happy to be here, to be at theOlympic Games. It's been a really long year and it does not take away from my accomplishments this year. Just missing out on one medal does not change who I am. It was just God's way of saying there is more to do and I just give God all the glory.\\\"  MORE ABOUT  Have your say...  1  Crime  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line train after youths told to stop vaping by middle-aged passenger  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line after youths told to stop vaping  2  Football  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup, confirmed tea